(Mac)
*INSTALL NODE*
If you have Homebrew, run:
	$brew install node

Otherwise, 
1. Install XCode (https://developer.apple.com/technologies/tools/)
2. Install Git (http://git-scm.com/book/en/Getting-Started-Installing-Git)
3. Run:
	$git clone git://github.com/ry/node.git
	$cd node
	$./configure
	$make
	$sudo make install

Then, type $node -v to ensure node has been successfully installed.

*INSTALL NPM & SOCKET.IO*
You can install NPM on Mac with one line in the terminal:
	$curl http://npmjs.org/install.sh | sh

	$cd /path/to/game/root
	$npm install socket.io


*START GAME SERVER*
	$cd /path/to/game/root
	$node game.js


*ABOUT THE GAME* 
Tutorial / Game demo taken from Robin Hawkes. http://rawkes.com/articles/creating-a-real-time-multiplayer-game-with-websockets-and-node.html

Canvas game that allows multiple users to interact in a single environment by using web sockets and node.

Next Steps: 
1) Add objects that randomly appear on stage to collect and add scoring
2) Add obstacles/maps
3) Add levels and increase difficulty
4) Add some art/backgrounds